article.headline: Auburn 67, Alabama A&amp,M 56
article.story: AUBURN, Ala. (AP) -- Korvotney Barber scored a game-high 19 points to lead Auburn to a 67-56 victory over Alabama A&M on Saturday. Rasheem Barrett had 12 points and Quantez Robertson had six points, nine rebounds and five assists for the Tigers (7-2). Auburn had a 27-4 run to take a 33-14 halftime lead. Alabama A&M (3-6) shot just 20.7 percent from the floor in the first half. Evan Hilton led Alabama A&M with 18 points and Trant Simpson added 17 points and six assists. Mickell Gladness, the nation's second leading shot blocker, had five points, eight rebounds and six blocks for Alabama A&M. Matt Heramb came off the bench with nine points for the Tigers in the first half. Dewayne Reed led Auburn with six assists. Alabama A&M pulled within 11 points twice in the second half, but Auburn held on for the win. The Bulldogs were short-handed because forward Jonathan Inman, the team's third leading scorer, separated his shoulder in their last practice and is out for the season.
